{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Song of Solomon 6 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:1",
      "text": "My beloved is gone down into his garden, to the bed of aromatical spices, to feed in the gardens, and to gather lilies.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:2",
      "text": "I to my beloved, and my beloved to me, who feedeth among the lilies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:3",
      "text": "Thou art beautiful, O my love, sweet and comely as Jerusalem terrible as an army set in array.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:4",
      "text": "Turn away thy eyes from me, for they have made me flee away. Thy hair is as a flock of goats, that appear from Galaad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:5",
      "text": "Thy teeth as a flock of sheep, which come up from the washing, all with twins, and there is none barren among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:6",
      "text": "Thy cheeks are as the bark of a pomegranate, beside what is hidden within thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:7",
      "text": "There are threescore queens, and fourscore concubines, and young maidens without number.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:8",
      "text": "One is my dove, my perfect one is but one, she is the only one of her mother, the chosen of her that bore her. The daughters saw her, and declared her most blessed: the queens and concubines, and they praised her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:9",
      "text": "Who is she that cometh forth as the morning rising, fair as the moon, bright as the sun, terrible as an army set in array?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:10",
      "text": "I went down into the garden of nuts, to see the fruits of the valleys, and to look if the vineyard had flourished, and the pomegranates budded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:11",
      "text": "I knew not: my soul troubled me for the chariots of Aminadab.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:song-of-solomon.6.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 6:12",
      "text": "Return, return, O Sulamitess: return, return that we may behold thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
